		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_47471305"><p>I don't think they think the "trifling" transgressions are "just as bad". I've never heard anyone say, or even suggest, that they are "just as bad".</p><p>On the other hand, I've seen very good evidence presented that the "trifling" transgressions tend to correlate strongly with environments in which people are a lot more comfortable pushing things a lot harder. which means that there is at least some reason to believe that they may <em>contribute to</em> an environment where people will think they can get away with rape. That, and "trifling" transgressions can have a significant cumulative effect over time.</p></div>
	</div>

