	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_47472833"><p>Another problem is sloppy wording of questions. Here is one example from the survey:</p><p><div class="quote"><p>32. Have you ever personally experienced inappropriate or sexual remarks, comments about physical beauty, cognitive sex differences, or other jokes, at an anthropological field site?</p></div><p>Technically, if somebody ever told you a joke about <b>anything</b> at a field site, then "yes" would be a valid answer, depending on how one interprets which parts of the sentence "inappropriate or sexual" applies to. The same applies to the other subclauses, like cognitive sex differences or beauty, both of which are completely valid subjects of discussion.</p><p>I think the questions asked here do very little to distinguish harassment<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
