	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_47472901"><p>Here's what problem I have with this, as someone who has written and implemented policies: The longer it is, and the more content that the reader thinks of as boring and "why the fuck do they even mention this?", the higher the chance it won't get read.</p><p>If you want your employees to actually read and know your policy, it must be short, to the point, and use redundancy very sparsely and intentionally.</p></div>
	</div>

