		<div id="comment_body_47472273"><p><div class="quote"><p>I'd imagine if I wore a v-neck that went half way to my naval to show off my manly chest hair and a codpiece at the next code review meeting it would certainly be considered sexual harassment.</p></div><p>What you're complaining about is the "harassment" that your female coworkers dress in a way that makes you want them so much you can't control yourself, not that what they're wearing would make them want to gouge their eyeballs out with a ball point pen. When you appreciate the difference between the two, you get to be a human being.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_47472273">

